TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {6956=He has won several writing and photography awards and was named Dairy Journalist of the Year in 1996 by Mid-America Dairymen, Inc., 7698=He joined the Hoard's staff in 1999 and helped launch the Hoard's WEST insert that is sent monthly to our readers in 17 Western States. Halladay is based in Meridian, Idaho, and is in charge of the editorial content and layout of each issue. His major areas of dairy interest are calf raising, technology, new facility design, animal crowding and behavior, cow cooling, dairy statistics, and trend analysis.}
